messages.message: <!channel> Jessica just merged a PR that allows creating/uploading files that have uri reserved characters like`#` in the file name in the file system UI. If you have an app that does file I/O, you might want to double check your code to see if the name is properly-encoded when making Ajax calls :slightly_smiling_face:
Does this mean URL encoding file paths in URIs or also post bodies?
file paths, we can send you examples of how we did it
In URLs or also post bodies though?
Just urls - when you make ajax calls with special characters in the url, they end up getting cut off
checkout where I put them in this PR: https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/9242/files#diff-c4ebca07c99e15f62b480161ddd860ee
would it be helpful for y'all (it might be for me) if I post a comment in asana when something satisfies a customer bug report or feature request?
I'm going to start tracking asana links inside of freshdesk for relevant engineering work related to tickets as well.
I don't want to create unnecessary noise though.
